      "slug": "chatgpt-vs-claude",
      "title": "ChatGPT vs Claude: Which AI Assistant Is Better in 2026?",
      "category": "Comparison",
      "date": "2026-06-16",
      "excerpt": "Deep comparison of OpenAI's ChatGPT and Anthropic's Claude — features, pricing, reasoning quality, and best use cases.",
      "content": `ChatGPT and Claude are the two most capable general-purpose AI assistants available today. Both excel at writing, reasoning, and answering questions — but they have distinct strengths that make one better than the other depending on your needs.\n\n## Quick Verdict\n\n- **Choose ChatGPT if:** You want the most versatile AI that handles any task, from creative writing to coding to data analysis. Its free tier is extremely generous.\n- **Choose Claude if:** You work with long documents, need superior reasoning quality, or prefer a cleaner, distraction-free interface.\n\n## Features Comparison\n\n| Feature | ChatGPT | Claude |\n|---------|---------|--------|\n| Context Window | 128K tokens | 200K tokens |\n| Free Tier | Excellent | Limited |\n| File Upload | Images, documents | Documents (limited on free) |\n| Coding | Strong with Copilot integration | Strong native |\n| Reasoning | Very strong | Exceptional |\n| Interface | Feature-rich | Clean and minimal |\n| Multimodal | Images, audio, video | Primarily text + images |\n\n## Reasoning Quality\n\nBoth models have undergone significant improvements in reasoning capabilities. Claude tends to produce more structured, well-organized responses — especially for analytical tasks. ChatGPT matches or exceeds Claude in creative tasks and general knowledge questions.\n\nFor research-heavy work, Claude's 200K context window is a significant advantage. You can paste an entire research paper and get coherent, well-structured analysis.\n\n## Pricing\n\nChatGPT offers a more generous free tier. ChatGPT Plus costs $20/month and includes access to GPT-4o. Claude's free tier has usage limits, while Claude Pro costs $20/month.\n\n## Bottom Line\n\nNeither is universally better. For everyday tasks, ChatGPT's versatility wins. For deep analysis and long-document work, Claude's reasoning and context window give it the edge.`
