      "date": "2026-06-16",
      "excerpt": "Grammarly catches errors while QuillBot rewrites your text. Understanding their differences helps you choose the right tool.",
      "content": `Grammarly and QuillBot solve different but complementary writing problems. Grammarly is best known for catching grammar, spelling, and punctuation errors. QuillBot specializes in paraphrasing and rewriting text.\n\n## Quick Verdict\n\n- **Choose Grammarly if:** You need real-time grammar checking and writing improvement suggestions.\n- **Choose QuillBot if:** You need to rewrite or rephrase existing text in different tones.\n\n## Core Strength\n\nGrammarly's browser extension works everywhere — Gmail, Google Docs, social media, Slack — catching errors in real-time. Its suggestions are clear and actionable, covering grammar, tone, clarity, and even style.\n\nQuillBot's paraphrasing engine offers multiple modes (standard, fluent, formal, concise, creative) that let you rewrite any text while preserving meaning. It's ideal for editors, students, and anyone who needs to rephrase content.\n\n## Limitations\n\nGrammarly is not designed for content creation — it only improves existing text. QuillBot similarly doesn't create content from scratch.\n\n## Bottom Line\n\nThey do different jobs. Many writers use both: Grammarly for proofreading, QuillBot for rewriting.`
