      "excerpt": "Notion AI offers an all-in-one workspace with AI features. Obsidian focuses on local-first, private note-taking. Which is right for you?",
      "content": `Notion and Obsidian represent two philosophies of knowledge management. Notion is a cloud-based all-in-one workspace with AI features. Obsidian is a local-first, privacy-focused note-taking app with powerful linking.\n\n## Quick Verdict\n\n- **Choose Notion if:** You want collaboration, AI features, and an all-in-one workspace.\n- **Choose Obsidian if:** Privacy, local storage, and deep knowledge linking are your priorities.\n\n## Collaboration\n\nNotion excels at team collaboration with real-time editing, comments, and shared workspaces. Obsidian is primarily a personal tool — collaboration requires third-party sync setups.\n\n## AI Features\n\nNotion AI provides writing assistance, summarization, translation, and brainstorming directly within your documents. Obsidian relies on community plugins for AI features.\n\n## Privacy\n\nObsidian stores all notes as local Markdown files on your device. Your data never leaves your machine. Notion stores everything in the cloud, which is convenient but means trusting a third party with your data.\n\n## Pricing\n\nNotion offers a generous free tier with AI features in paid plans. Obsidian is completely free for personal use.\n\n## Bottom Line\n\nNotion for teams and AI-enhanced productivity. Obsidian for individuals who value privacy and deep knowledge linking.`
